{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "auth-set-password-e2e",
    "name": "Auth – Set Password (POST /api/v1/profile/set-password)",
    "description": "E2E tests for POST /api/v1/profile/set-password (requires JWT).\n\nFolder execution order (orchestrated by make e2e-set-password):\n  1. setup             — register gmail_test_email, fetch verification OTP from Gmail, verify email, login\n  2. failures          — password_already_set (registered user has a password_hash → 422);\n                         empty new_password → 422; too-short new_password → 422 (representative strength case)\n  3. auth-failures     — missing Authorization header → 401; tampered token signature → 401\n  4. validation        — body > 1 MiB → 413; malformed JSON → 422\n  5. rate-limiting-spw — registers a dedicated +spwrl Gmail alias user for a fresh spw:usr: bucket,\n                         then: 5 warmups → 6th → 429 (Retry-After: 180)\n\nRate-limiter design note:\n  The spw:usr: limiter is user-keyed, not IP-keyed. The failures and validation folders consume\n  all 5 slots of spw_access_token's bucket before rate-limiting-spw runs. To give the RL folder\n  a fresh bucket, it registers a dedicated gmail_test_email+spwrl alias user (spw_rl_access_token).\n  Gmail delivers +spwrl mail to the same inbox; the OTP fetch targets the alias with a to: filter.\n\nAll test users use @e2e.test emails (or gmail_test_email) so `make _e2e-db-clean` can wipe them.\nRun `make _e2e-db-clean` and `make _e2e-kv-clean` before this collection.\n\nNotes on what is NOT covered here and why:\n  - T-01: Happy path (OAuth-only user successfully sets a password):\n      Requires a JWT for a user with password_hash IS NULL. There is no standard email+password\n      login path for such a user (they have no password to present). Exercising this path E2E\n      would require a real OAuth provider callback (Google/Telegram) to obtain a JWT. This case\n      is fully covered by service_test.go TestService_SetPassword/happy_path and\n      store_test.go TestSetPasswordHashTx_Integration/T-01/T-18/T-19.\n  - T-04/T-05: not_found (user row deleted between GET and SET):\n      Requires a race between two concurrent requests; not reproducible in Newman. Covered by\n      service_test.go TestService_SetPassword/get_user_not_found and ghost_user_in_tx.\n  - Individual password-strength rule variants (no-upper, no-lower, no-digit, no-symbol, >72 bytes):\n      Covered by handler_test.go; one representative E2E case (too short) confirms wiring.\n  - Audit row event type and DB-level content: covered by store_test.go T-18/T-19.\n  - context.WithoutCancel absence (D-09): covered by service_test.go.\n  - QuerierProxy error injection: covered by store_test.go.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Increment the request sequence counter and derive a unique X-Forwarded-For IP",
          "// for every request so non-RL folders never exhaust any rate-limit bucket.",
          "// The rate-limiting folder uses the same token (and therefore same user-ID bucket)",
          "// regardless of _xff, because the limiter is user-keyed, not IP-keyed.",
          "// Requires TRUSTED_PROXIES=127.0.0.1/32 in .env.",
          "const n = (pm.collectionVariables.get('_req_seq') | 0) + 1;",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_req_seq', n);",
          "const ip = '10.' + ((n>>16)&0xff) + '.' + ((n>>8)&0xff) + '.' + (n&0xff);",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_xff', ip);"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "setup",
      "description": "Registers the gmail_test_email user, fetches the verification OTP from Gmail, verifies the email, and logs in. All subsequent folders depend on spw_access_token being set.\n\nNote: This user is registered with a password (P@ssw0rd1!) and is therefore NOT an OAuth-only account. The set-password route will return 422 password_already_set for this user, which is tested in the failures folder. See the collection description for why the true OAuth happy path cannot be covered here.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /register → 201 (setup account)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const email = pm.environment.get('gmail_test_email');",
                  "if (!email) {",
                  "    console.error('[ERROR] gmail_test_email not set in environment — add it to environment.json.');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('spw_email', email);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('spw_password', 'P@ssw0rd1!');",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('spw_new_password', 'NewSpwP@ss2!');"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('message field present and non-empty', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "",
                  "// --- Gmail verification OTP fetch ---",
                  "const token = pm.variables.get('gmail_access_token');",
                  "if (!token) { console.warn('[WARN] gmail_access_token not set — skipping Gmail fetch'); return; }",
                  "",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Waiting 8 s for verification email to arrive in Gmail...');",
                  "const start = Date.now();",
                  "while (Date.now() - start < 8000) {}",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Done waiting. Querying Gmail API...');",
                  "",
                  "const spwEmail = pm.collectionVariables.get('spw_email');",
                  "const query = encodeURIComponent('subject:\"Verify your\" to:' + spwEmail + ' newer_than:1h');",
                  "pm.sendRequest({",
                  "    url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages?q=' + query + '&maxResults=3',",
                  "    method: 'GET',",
                  "    header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token }",
                  "}, (err, res) => {",
                  "    if (err) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail list failed:', err); return; }",
                  "    if (res.code === 401) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail token expired — refresh at https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground'); return; }",
                  "    const msgs = res.json().messages;",
                  "    if (!msgs || !msgs.length) { console.warn('[WARN] No matching verification email found in Gmail.'); return; }",
                  "    pm.sendRequest({",
                  "        url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages/' + msgs[0].id + '?format=full',",
                  "        method: 'GET',",
                  "        header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token }",
                  "    }, (err2, res2) => {",
                  "        if (err2) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail fetch failed:', err2); return; }",
                  "        const msg = res2.json();",
                  "        let body = '';",
                  "        const parts = msg.payload && msg.payload.parts;",
                  "        if (parts && parts.length) {",
                  "            const p = parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/plain') || parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/html');",
                  "            if (p && p.body && p.body.data) body = atob(p.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/'));",
                  "        } else if (msg.payload && msg.payload.body && msg.payload.body.data) {",
                  "            body = atob(msg.payload.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/'));",
                  "        }",
                  "        if (!body) { console.warn('[WARN] Could not decode verification email body.'); return; }",
                  "        const match = body.match(/\\b(\\d{6})\\b/);",
                  "        if (!match) { console.warn('[WARN] No 6-digit OTP found in verification email.'); return; }",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('spw_vfy_code', match[1]);",
                  "        console.log('[INFO] Verification OTP stored in spw_vfy_code:', match[1]);",
                  "    });",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"display_name\": \"SpwSetup\", \"email\": \"{{spw_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{spw_password}}\"}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /verify-email → 200 (consume verification OTP)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const code = pm.collectionVariables.get('spw_vfy_code');",
                  "if (!code) {",
                  "    console.error('[ERROR] spw_vfy_code is empty — Gmail fetch in register step did not complete.');",
                  "    console.error('        Check: gmail_access_token is set, token not expired, --delay-request >= 8000.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('message includes \"verified\"', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.include('verified'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"email\": \"{{spw_email}}\", \"code\": \"{{spw_vfy_code}}\"}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/verify-email",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "verify-email"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /login → 200 (store access token)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('access_token present', () => pm.expect(body.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('spw_access_token', body.access_token);",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Access token stored in spw_access_token.');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"{{spw_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{spw_password}}\"}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "failures",
      "description": "Domain-error and validation-failure paths for POST /set-password.\nAll requests use spw_access_token (set in setup/login).\n\nThe most important case here is password_already_set: it proves that the entire\nroute is wired correctly (JWT auth → service → store → correct domain error).\nThe registered user has a password_hash, so the service correctly rejects the request.\n\nNOTE: These 3 requests consume 3 of the 5 spw:usr: bucket slots for spw_access_token.\nThe validation folder consumes the remaining 2. The rate-limiting-spw folder therefore\nuses a dedicated second user (spw_rl_access_token) with its own fresh bucket.\n\nNOT covered here (see unit/integration tests):\n  - T-01: OAuth happy path — see collection description.\n  - T-04/T-05: not_found race condition — not reproducible in Newman.\n  - Each individual strength rule variant (no-upper, no-lower, no-digit, no-symbol):\n      covered by handler_test.go; too-short below is the representative E2E wiring check.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /set-password → 422 password_already_set (registered user already has a password)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// The setup user was registered with a password (password_hash IS NOT NULL in DB).",
                  "// GetUserForSetPassword returns HasNoPassword=false → service returns ErrPasswordAlreadySet.",
                  "// Handler maps ErrPasswordAlreadySet → 422 password_already_set.",
                  "// This is the most meaningful wiring test: JWT auth → service guard → correct HTTP error.",
                  "pm.test('status is 422', () => pm.response.to.have.status(422));",
                  "pm.test('code is password_already_set', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('password_already_set');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{spw_access_token}}"
              },
              { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"new_password\": \"{{spw_new_password}}\"}",
