    {
      "name": "rate-limiting-spw",
      "description": "Verifies the spw:usr: user rate limiter for POST /set-password (burst=5, rate=5/15 min).\n\nWhy a dedicated user (spw_rl_access_token):\n  The spw:usr: limiter is user-keyed. The failures folder (3 requests) and validation folder\n  (2 requests) each use spw_access_token, exhausting all 5 slots of that user's bucket before\n  this folder runs. To get a fresh burst=5 bucket, this folder registers and logs in as a\n  separate gmail_test_email+spwrl alias user (spw_rl_access_token). Gmail delivers +spwrl\n  mail to the same inbox; the OTP fetch targets the alias with a to: filter.\n\nSequence:\n  rl-setup 1–3: register +spwrl alias → verify email (Gmail OTP) → login (store spw_rl_access_token)\n  warmup  1–5:  not 429 (slots 1–5 consumed; each returns 422 due to password_already_set,\n                but the rate limiter fires first so slots are consumed regardless)\n  6th request → 429 rate_limited (bucket exhausted)\n\nRetry-After = ceil(1 / (5/900)) = ceil(180) = 180 seconds.\n\nCovers checklist item: 6th request from same user within 15 min → 429 (spw:usr:, burst=5).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "rl-setup 1/3 — POST /register → 201 (+spwrl alias user)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Derive the +spwrl Gmail alias from gmail_test_email.",
                  "// Gmail delivers user+spwrl@gmail.com to the same inbox as user@gmail.com.",
                  "const base = pm.environment.get('gmail_test_email');",
                  "if (!base) { console.error('[ERROR] gmail_test_email not set'); }",
                  "const at = base.indexOf('@');",
                  "const rlEmail = base.slice(0, at) + '+spwrl' + base.slice(at);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('spw_rl_email', rlEmail);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('spw_rl_password', 'RlSpwP@ss1!');"
                ]
